# === Claude Code / planwright local state ===
#
# Policy: denylist, not a blanket ignore. Shared project config is committed
# (.claude/settings.json, .claude/commands/, .claude/agents/, and planwright's
# tracked default config); only personal/per-machine/transient state is ignored.

# Per-user personal overrides (Claude Code convention).
.claude/settings.local.json

# planwright per-repo local config — agent-maintained override (design.md D-33:
# per-repo/personal overrides, thresholds). Not committed.
.claude/*.local.yml
.claude/*.local.json

# Machine-local overlay layer (customization-overlay D-1/D-4): the highest,
# per-machine, UNCOMMITTED overlay layer ships as `<kind>.local/` directories
# (doctrine.local/, catalogs.local/). They must never be committed — that is
# the trust boundary the machine-local layer depends on, and the only guard
# against secrets in uncommitted overlays (R9; the secret scanner covers
# committed files only). The `.local.*` file globs above match files, not
# these directories, so ignore them explicitly.
.claude/*.local/

# Machine-local environment layer (mise convention). Loaded by mise in this
# checkout and, via ancestor-directory config loading, in every worktree under
# .claude/worktrees/. Per-machine paths and session plumbing only.
mise.local.toml
.mise.local.toml

# Linked git worktrees created by /orchestrate (design.md D-37). Working copies,
# not source.
.claude/worktrees/

# Generated /spec-walkthrough comprehension artifacts (design.md D-8, REQ-E1.1).
# Self-contained HTML renders of a spec bundle — ephemeral, per-reader, and
# regenerable from the bundle; never source. Kept out of the tree so a render in
# any checkout (the command's one sanctioned write) leaves the tracked tree clean.
.claude/walkthroughs/

# Optional handover brief — transient per-worktree cache (design.md D-2/D-3).
.claude/handover.md

# Per-spec advisory lock (design.md D-10) — transient runtime state taken by
# /orchestrate and the tasks-pr-sync hook around tasks.md writes, plus the
# hook's atomic-write temp files (orphaned only by an unclean kill).
specs/*/.orchestrate.lock
specs/*/.tasks-pr-sync.*

# Runtime dispatch markers (orchestration-concurrency D-1/D-3) — the timestamped
# per-task markers /orchestrate drops as part of the dispatch record. Discardable
# local state, never committed: keeping them out of the tree is what lets `main`
# carry no dispatch commit, so a worker worktree cut from it inherits nothing
# foreign (REQ-A1.2 contamination isolation by construction).
specs/*/.orchestrate/

# === Bootstrap staging ===

# Consumed bootstrap seed — already mined into specs/bootstrap/, kept local only.
specs/_pending/notes.md

# reference/ is tracked for now (bootstrap execution tasks cite it as their
# migration source). It is transient and SCHEDULED FOR HISTORY PURGE before any
# public release — it may contain personal/work data. See tasks.md "Deferred".
